2. Use Fiddler’s Breakpoint Feature

If you can’t disable auto-login, you can set breakpoints in Fiddler to pause the request and give you time to modify it.

Here’s how to use Fiddler’s Breakpoint feature:
	1.	Open Fiddler and make sure it’s capturing traffic.
	2.	Go to Rules → Customize Rules in the Fiddler menu. This will open the CustomRules.js file.
	3.	Find the OnBeforeRequest function in the file. Add the following code to break the request before it’s sent to PlayFab:
